narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: A 10/10 course. The subject this year was Hindi poetry - an extremely fascinating and colorful subject. Students were part of the material-selection process (a first for me at Yale) and this really sparked a strong interest in class-discussions. While this was a formal overview of the world of Hindi poetry, the material prompted certain questions that applied to poetry as a form of expression - a theme that transcends language. So in a great way, this course was intensely specific but also surprisingly broad.
Take it if you want to gain a slightly nuanced understanding of a particular topic in Hindi.
